Disruption of the Neurotoxic Cascade: Heavy metals act as catalyst triggers for massive oxidative stress in the brain. They activate microglial cells, which produce pro-inflammatory cytokines (like TNF-\uc0\u945  and IL-1\u946 ) that lead to neurodegeneration. By binding these metals into stable, water-soluble complexes, EDTA cuts off the source of this inflammatory loop. [1("https://www.laballey.com/chemicals/acids/EDTA?srsltid=AfmBOor_sTi9uEejNFxzaUXB7B4JHOfNVl7SBzAcrY7s7ybGFYd5gleq")]\
